defs.name: El
defs.value: El { name, is_text, paired, attributes, style, content }

defs.name: text
defs.docs:
Creates a new element that displays its name as text and nothing else
 when formatted. This is useful for making innerHTML something other
 than a tag, such as inside the <style> or <script> tags.

defs.name: attributes
defs.docs: Takes a slice of Attr as input and pushes each member onto .attributes vec.

defs.name: style
defs.docs: Takes a slice of Prop as input and pushes each member onto .style vec.

defs.name: content
defs.docs: Takes a slice of El and pushes each element onto .content.

defs.name: id_find
defs.docs: Allows for finding a child element by its id attribute.

defs.name: Page
defs.docs:
The Page struct.
 Stores a list of nested HTML elements.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Returns a new Page. Takes a slice of El as input.

defs.name: add
defs.docs: Pushes an El onto content field vec.

defs.name: id_find
defs.docs: Allows for finding a child element by its id attribute.

defs.name: format
defs.docs:
Formats the Page for display or storage. Automatically
 prepends '<!DOCTYPE HTML> to the beginning of the file.
